[code:2jkeb216]
msg (&quot;Ask player random yes or no question&#46;&quot;)
get input {
     if (result = &quot;yes&quot;) {
          msg (&quot;Hooray!&quot;)
     }
     else {
          msg (&quot;You suck!&quot;)
     }
}
[/code:2jkeb216]

I would suggest modifying it so that:

if (result = &quot;yes&quot;) {

becomes

if (StartsWith (LCase (result), &quot;y&quot;)) {

This will then interprete &quot;Yes&quot;, &quot;yay&quot;, &quot;Yeah&quot; and &quot;y&quot; to mean yes too.

